headline: 2 Reasons to Like YUM and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: While the broader market has struggled with the S&P 500 down 1.7% since October 2024, Yum! Brands has surged ahead as its stock price has climbed by 13.6% to $158.53 per share. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
